    "love_response": "```python\ndef is_palindrome(s: str) -> bool:\n    cleaned = \"\".join(c.lower() for c in s if c.isalnum())\n    return cleaned == cleaned[::-1]\n```\n\nHandles the main edge cases:\n- **Case**: `\"Racecar\"` \u2192 True\n- **Spaces/punctuation**: `\"A man, a plan, a canal: Panama\"` \u2192 True\n- **Empty string**: `\"\"` \u2192 True (vacuously)\n- **Single char**: `\"a\"` \u2192 True\n\nIf you want strict (no cleaning, spaces and case matter), it's even simpler:\n\n```python\ndef is_palindrome(s: str) -> bool:\n    return s == s[::-1]\n```\n\nThe `[::-1]` slice reverses the string \u2014 that's the bit people often second-guess themselves on.",
